results.name: Sum of prime indices of the n-th squarefree number.
comment: A prime index of n is a number m such that prime(m) divides n.
example: The 19th squarefree number is 30 with prime indices (3,2,1), so a(19) = 6.
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Sep 15 2018
